<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Talbot" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Talbot,</orth> 1) name of the renowned English general in the French wars of the fifteenth century: <bibl n="shak. h5 4.3.54" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 3, 54</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.106" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 106</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.106" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 106</bibl> 128 <emph>(a T.! a T.!</emph> cf. <cit><quote>A).</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.4.23" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 4, 23</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.2.37" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 37</bibl> and <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.3.20" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 20</bibl> <cit><quote>(the T.).</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 3</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>(John T.).</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.7.61" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 7, 61</bibl></cit> (his various titles enumerated) etc. etc. 2) his son John T.: <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.3.35" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 3, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.5.1" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 1</bibl> etc. 3) Sir Gilbert T., a partisan of Richmond: <bibl n="shak. r3 4.5.10" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 5, 10</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>